snippet.title: 2014 FIFA World Cup Brazil (PS3 gameplay 6/12) - Story of Finals
snippet.description:
Oto szósty materiał wideo, w którym prezentuję Wam grę 2014 FIFA World Cup Brazil. Nie jest to pełnoprawna seria "Zagrajmy w 2014 FIFA World Cup Brazil", tylko gameplay z pełnej wersji. Dzisiaj pokażę Wam tryb "Story of Finals", w którym rozegramy końcówkę meczu Iran - Nigeria z fazy grupowej Mistrzostw Świata. 2014 FIFA World Cup Brazil zadebiutowało w naszym kraju 17 kwietnia 2014 roku za sprawą firmy Electronic Arts Polska na PlayStation 3 oraz Xboksie 360.

2014 FIFA World Cup Brazil to specjalna odsłona popularnej serii symulatorów piłki nożnej. Produkcja jest w całości poświęcona zbliżającym się Mistrzostwom Świata w Piłce Nożnej 2014, które odbędą się w dniach 12 czerwca - 13 lipca w Brazylii. Gra pozwala na wzięcie udziału w kwalifikacjach oraz samym turnieju, a także oferuje wiele innych trybów rozgrywki. No i jak zwykle dla graczy to świetna okazja, by wraz z Reprezentacją Polski zdobyć Puchar Świata, choćby wirtualnie;).

Muzyka z intra:
David Correy - "The World Is Ours"

Ο ζηλιάρης Βαγγέλης προφανώς και δε μπορεί να βάλει γκολ, παίζοντας κατενάτσιο, η Μαντώ εισβάλει στο στούντιο να δει τι γίνεται και ο Δημήτρης προσπαθεί απλά... να κερδίσει!

snippet.title: CBC is your home for the 2014 FIFA World Cup! | CBC Toronto
snippet.description:
From June 12 - July 13, CBC has the FIFA World Cup covered on CBC Television and online. 
At our dedicated website http://cbc.ca/fifaworldcup, you can stream all the games live & on-demand, find news, schedules, results and more. On Twitter, follow @cbcsports and use hashtag #CBCWorldCup. Download the CBC 2014 FIFA World Cup App free for iOS & Android. Join us July 12-13 for CIBC Soccer Nation as it makes the final stop of its national tour in Toronto -- a public viewing party with live performances, food, activities and more, at the Canadian Broadcasting Centre on Front Street!

snippet.title: Bend it to the Goal - FIFA World Cup Song 2014
snippet.description:
32 Nations... 32 x 11 Players... 32 x 11 x million fans... its not just  a game.. its a madness... a feeling! and the wait is over... 
With 90 min to decide your fate, you have no choice but to bring everything you got into the game, because its upto you to bend it to the goal!

snippet.title: Contra A Copa: The Other Side of Brazil's World Cup (Full Length)
snippet.description:
Subscribe to VICE News here: http://bit.ly/Subscribe-to-VICE-News

Although it might have seemed like a good idea to host the 2014 FIFA World Cup in Brazil — one of the most soccer-obsessed countries in the world — massive social unrest has taken the country by storm in the lead-up to the tournament.

The Brazilian government is spending an estimated $14 billion on this year's tournament, making it the most expensive World Cup to date. This has provoked outrage among Brazilians, many of whom view the government as corrupt, and are now seeing vast amounts of money being spent on soccer stadiums and police, while the country's endemic poverty and social issues are ignored.

This growing unrest led to violent anti-government protests breaking out in June of 2013, which have continued with increasing momentum in the lead-up to the World Cup. The Brazilian government has responded to these demonstrations by deploying massive numbers of police and military throughout the country in an attempt to suppress the masses. Despite this crackdown, major demonstrations continue to take place in cities across the country as international teams begin to arrive for the games.
 
VICE News traveled to Brazil to see how the country is preparing for one of the world's biggest international events, while simultaneously struggling to control a mounting civil uprising.

snippet.title: FIFA World Cup 2014. Destination: Belo Horizonte, Estádio Mineirão
snippet.description:
Since the 18th century, during the days of the Inconfidência Mineira - an independence conspiracy against the domination of the Portuguese crown - the state of Minas Gerais gambled with the idea of instating a new capital to replace Ouro Preto. 

The number one question when someone meets a belo-horizontino is often the same: Atletico Mineiro or Cruzeiro? The city is in love with football and lives under a constant atmosphere of rivalry between two of the top contenders in Brazilian football: Clube Atlético Mineiro, the Galo (Rooster), and Cruzeiro Esporte Clube, also known as the Raposa (Fox). América Futebol Clube, the Coelho (Rabbit), is also a traditional state rival and has had its successful surges over the years.

One of the most historic venues in Brazilian football and called home by Atletico Mineiro and Cruzeiro, the 58,170 capacity Estadio Mineirao is set to undergo a complete overhaul prior to the 2014 FIFA World Cup. 

Belo Horizonte FIFA World Cup Game Schedule:

Match  Date / Time  Stage     Results

snippet.title: FIFA World Cup 2014 Song - Yo Puedo (Tiempos de Libertad)
snippet.description:
La Canción "Yo Puedo" (Tiempos de Libertad) 2014 
Hugo Ft. Adan Castillo Esta Disponible a la Venta YA! Adquiere lo en iTunes, amazon o a través del enlace siguiente http://www.cdbaby.com/cd/hugo5

La Vida es como la Luz de la Aurora
Que Llega hasta ser perfecta
como la semilla que cae y da su fruto a su tiempo
No pierdas la fe y el amor
conviertete un ganador
mira la hermosura del mundo
y seras un triudnfador

//Si si si yo puedo
y a nada le temo
No no me detengo
Voy detrás de mi Sueño//

Tu eres como la sonrisa de un Niño
que radia inocencia
como la pupila que brilla
Llena de esperanza
no pierdas la fe ni el amor
tu ya eres un ganador
siente la hermosura del mundo
que ya eres un Triunfador

//Si si si yo puedo
y a nada le temo
No no me detengo
Voy detrás de mi Sueño//

Esta es tu Vida
Y son Tiempos de Libertad
Mira hacia arriba
No dudes que vas a ganar
No te detengas,
Que el fruto ya esta por dar
Eres una estrella
Creelo que vas a Triunfar

//Si si si yo puedo
y a nada le temo
No no me detengo
Voy detras de mi Sueño//

HOY ES TU MOMENTO,
HOY ES EL TIEMPO!

snippet.title: Mark Haskins analysis Sunday FIFA World Cup matches
snippet.description: The action and could not have been scripted better... Algeria powered into World Cup history scoring 4 goals, a first for an African nation and Group G, the famed Group of death is heading towards a thrilling finale, with endless permutations abounding after Portugal scored a late second goal to equalise against the USA. And Belgium scored an unconvincing1 -nil win against Russia. Our resident analyst, Mark Haskins will take us through this action.

Le peuple Brésilien proteste depuis plusieurs années contre la coupe du monde qui va avoir lieu chez eux, au Brésil.
La raison principale est que plus de 3/4 du financement de la coupe du monde vient de fonds publics qui auraient pu être utilisés dans des structures plus importantes comme l'éducation et les hôpitaux, il y a trop souvent pas assez de place et de moyen pour soigner les blessés.

snippet.title: Luís Figo - Dare to Predict - FIFA World Cup
snippet.description:
Watch Luís Figo's #DareToPredict video. Now make a video reply with your predictions to our 5 World Cup questions for the chance to win top signed prizes.

Luís Figo is a Portuguese retired professional footballer who played as a midfielder for Sporting CP, Barcelona, Real Madrid and Inter Milan. He won 127 caps for the Portugal national team, a one-time record that has since been bettered by Cristiano Ronaldo and João Moutinho. His 106 assists are the second-most in La Liga history, behind Lionel Messi. He won the 2000 Ballon d'Or, 2001 FIFA World Player of the Year, and in 2004 Pelé named him in the FIFA 100 list of the world's greatest living players.

Figo had a successful career highlighted by several trophy wins, including the Portuguese Cup, four La Liga titles, two Spanish Cups, three Spanish Super Cups, one UEFA Champions League title, one UEFA Cup Winners' Cup, two UEFA Super Cups, one Intercontinental Cup, four Serie A titles, one Italian Cup and three Italian Super Cups. At international level, he scored 32 goals for Portugal, representing the nation at three European Championships and two World Cups, helping them reach the final but finish as runners-up at Euro 2004. Figo is regarded as one of the greatest players from his generation, and one of the best Portuguese footballers of all time.

snippet.title: FIFA World Cup 2014. Destination: Fortaleza, Estádio Castelão
snippet.description:
Although it was officially founded as a village in 1726, and would only become the capital of Ceará in 1799, Fortaleza (Portuguese for 'fortress') owes its name to the period between 1637 to 1654, when it was controlled by the Dutch, who built the Schoonenborch Fort. 

Two of the most popular clubs from the north-east of Brazil come from Fortaleza: Ceara Sporting Club and Fortaleza Esporte Clube. Both teams have historically shared the attention of the fans throughout the whole state of Ceará, as well as the state titles. 

Thanks to the 2014 FIFA World Cup Brazil, the main football stadium in the city of Fortaleza, home to both Ceara and Fortaleza, will be entirely refurbished. 

Fortaleza FIFA World Cup Game Schedule:

Match  Date / Time  Stage     Results   
7  14 June / 16:00  Group D  Uruguay - Costa Rica
17  17 June / 16:00  Group A  Brazil - Mexico
29  21 June / 16:00  Group G  Germany - Ghana
38  24 June / 17:00  Group C  Greece - Ivory Coast
51  29 June / 13:00  Roud of 16  1B - 2A
57  04 July / 17:00  Quarterfinals  W49 - W50

#wc2014brasil #WC2014 #Fortaleza #football

snippet.title: World Cup 2014: Brazilian soccer fans turn the table on Mexican soccer players by calling them fags
snippet.description: "Eeeeh.... PUTO!" is a chant often heard at Mexican soccer stadiums shouted by fans at the top of their lungs to call opponents 'fags.' At the 2014 World Cup match between host team Brazil and Mexico the Brazilian fans turned the tables on Mexico and shouted the chant at them. Mexican soccer fans were not too enthused and took to social media to insult Brazilians in return.

snippet.title: 2014 FIFA World Cup Wingsuit Flight Over Rio de Janeiro - GOOOOOOOAL!
snippet.description:
http://www.epictv.com
BUY EPIC GEAR, TESTED BY THE BEST: GoPro, Sony, DJI, ION, Magicam, Optrix, Hitcase and more 
http://shop.epictv.com

We don't play much football/soccer here at EpicTV but that doesn't mean we don't want to support one of the greatest sporting events on Earth, the 2014 FIFA World Cup in Brazil. We got in touch with California-based British wingsuit maker Tony Uragallo and asked him to make us some special suits for the occasion. We then hooked up EpicTV athlete and citizen of the world Jhonathan Florez with a couple of Uragallo's finest threads and sent him down to Rio de Janeiro for one awesome Wingsuit flight. snippet.title: GOALS USA vs Ghana 2014 FIFA WORLD CUP SOCCER
snippet.description:
United States DESTROY Ghana 2-1 in a thrilling encounter of FIFA World Cup. 
An early Clint Dempsey goal kick-started things for United States as the they beat Ghana 2-1 in their World Cup Group G clash. Playing four hours after Germany beat Portugal 4-0 to go on top, both sides knew they had to make it count in the encounter. And USA did.

Dempsey scored the first goal within just 30 seconds before his side defended the slender lead until Ghana pulled one back in the 82nd minute. United States didn't fall flat though and kept pushing ahead, believing they could get another one. A corner kick taken by substitute Graham Zusi was met by his fellow substitute-teammate John Brook's head to grab the winner.

Ghana started without stars Kevin-Prince Boateng and Michael Essien and missed the finishing touch up-front as they were stunned by FIFA World Cup 2014′s earliest goal yet. As soon as Boateng came on in the second-half, the Black Stars looked potent in their attacks and the equalizer soon came through Ayew's effort.

German-born Brooks' winner is his first goal for his adopted country and the win made Jurgen Klinsmann's 50th match in charge of the United States a memorable one.

The victory also avenged defeats to Ghana in the past two World Cups, the latter when Ghana went on to the quarter-finals.

snippet.title: FIFA World Cup Viewing at Odyssey at Epcot; Soccer Goofy & Donald Topiary; Merchandise & Activities
snippet.description:
Topiary Soccer Goofy is still on display after his run at the Epcot Flower and Garden Festival for the FIFA World Cup! In addition, viewing is held daily at the Odyssey (former restaurant), with a grab-and-go area for snacks, sandwiches and drinks. There is a wide variety of merchandise, including soccer Mickey kicking a ball that looks like Spaceship Earth! Kids can also kick around a soccer ball in World Showcase near Germany.

snippet.title: Luis Suarez Faking his injury World Cup 2014
snippet.description:
The most ruthless soccer players often use their hands or elbows or knees to rough up opposing players. The most reckless — or dirtiest — might even use their cleats. Then there is Luis Suárez.

Suárez, the Uruguayan striker who has emerged as one of the best players in the world over the past year, is a biter. And, it seems, a serial one.

For the third time in his career, Suárez is facing potential punishment for appearing to sink his teeth into an opponent. This time, it happened on the biggest soccer stage of all, the World Cup, during Uruguay's 1-0 victory over Italy on Tuesday. Late in the second half, Suárez bumped into Giorgio Chiellini, an Italian defender, while jockeying for position in the penalty area and then dropped his head into Chiellini's shoulder. Chiellini immediately recoiled as both fell to the ground.

snippet.title: 2014 FIFA World Cup Brazil (PS3 gameplay 5/12) - Brazylia vs Chorwacja (mecz otwarcia)
snippet.description:
Oto piąty materiał wideo, w którym prezentuję Wam grę 2014 FIFA World Cup Brazil. Nie jest to pełnoprawna seria "Zagrajmy w 2014 FIFA World Cup Brazil", tylko gameplay z pełnej wersji. Dzisiaj oficjalnie rozpoczynają się Mistrzostwa Świata 2014, więc z tej okazji postanowiłem rozegrać sobie mecz otwarcia (Brazylia - Chorwacja), który dziś o godzinie 22:00 rozpocznie się na stadionie w Sao Paulo. 2014 FIFA World Cup Brazil zadebiutowało w naszym kraju 17 kwietnia 2014 roku za sprawą firmy Electronic Arts Polska na PlayStation 3 oraz Xboksie 360.

2014 FIFA World Cup Brazil to specjalna odsłona popularnej serii symulatorów piłki nożnej. Produkcja jest w całości poświęcona zbliżającym się Mistrzostwom Świata w Piłce Nożnej 2014, które odbędą się w dniach 12 czerwca - 13 lipca w Brazylii. Gra pozwala na wzięcie udziału w kwalifikacjach oraz samym turnieju, a także oferuje wiele innych trybów rozgrywki. No i jak zwykle dla graczy to świetna okazja, by wraz z Reprezentacją Polski zdobyć Puchar Świata, choćby wirtualnie;).

Muzyka z intra:
David Correy - "The World Is Ours"

snippet.title: FIFA World Cup 2014. Destination: Natal, Arena das Dunas
snippet.description:
On 25 December 1597, back when Brazil was a colony of the Portuguese crown, a group of Portuguese officials reached the Potengi River with the duty of reclaiming the captaincy of Rio Grande do Norte, which was then dominated by French buccaneers. 

The top three teams in the state of Rio Grande do Norte are from Natal: Alecrim Futebol Clube and the city's two powerhouses and eternal rivals, America Futebol Clube and ABC Futebol Clube. Both teams have shared the vast majority of trophies of the Campeonato Potiguar ('Potiguar' being one who comes from Rio Grande do Norte) and were regulars in the Campeonato Brasileiro's elite until the mid-1980s. ABC have not competed in the top tier since, meanwhile América have had their share of successful spurts and even won the regional title of the North-East Cup in 1998. 

Ever since it was inaugurated back in 1972, the Estadio Joao Claudio de Vasconcelos Machado -- better known as the Machadão -- has welcomed the biggest clashes in Natal football to the Lagoa Nova neighbourhood. 

Natal FIFA World Cup Game Schedule:

Match  Date / Time  Stage    Results   
2  13 June / 13:00  Group A  Mexico - Cameroon
14  16 June / 19:00  Group G  Ghana - USA
22  19 June / 19:00  Group C  Japan - Greece
39  24 June / 13:00  Group D  Italy - Uruguay

#wc2014brasil #WC2014 #Natal #football
http://www.teleprostir.com

snippet.title: Greektown Mania Hits Toronto in FIFA World Cup Win
snippet.description: The Greeks played to their strengths, especially their defensive tactics, absorbing pressure, hitting back and flooding centre field when it mattered.  It was standing room only outside Trapezzi as the overflowing crowd gathered and enjoyed a triumphant victory as only the Greeks can do. This was a tight and dramatic game (Greece-Ivory Coast 2-1). Police were present as people took to the streets bringing World Cup mania to the Danforth. A sea of blue and white flags, horns and chants in Greek could be heard throughout the neighbourood as a procession of cars lined Logan Avenue.
tags: Greektown World Cup Soccer Anita Barber Photography

Hello mes beautés, aujourd'hui j'ai le plaisir de revenir avec un tutoriel maquillage 'd'été' avec pour thème le brésil. C'est pour cela que j'ai créé un maquillage chargé, super colorée avec des faux cils plus voyant que d'habitude bref, un maquillage de carnaval,festival ect.. N'oubliez pas d'aimer la vidéo pour plus de tutoriels, de vous abonnez à ma chaîne et de me suivre sur les réseaux sociaux. Bisous♥ 



Hello my beauties, today I am pleased to return with a "pop of color" summer makeup tutorial with the theme brazil. This is why I created a makeup loaded with super colorful false eyelashes more light than usual brief, makeup carnival festival ect .. Do not forget to like the video for more tutorials , you subscribe to my channel and follow me on social networks. Kisses♥

-----------------------------------------

PALETTES :
----------------


- Sleek: "Divine - ACID 570"




- BH Cosmetics: "26 Colorpalette neutral eyeshadow/blush"




- Coastal scents: "88 Ultra Shimmer"



- Eyeliner: L.A Colors "Black"

snippet.title: 2014 FIFA World Cup Brazil (PS3 gameplay 7/12) - Belgia vs Rosja (faza grupowa)
snippet.description:
Oto siódmy materiał wideo, w którym prezentuję Wam grę 2014 FIFA World Cup Brazil. Nie jest to pełnoprawna seria "Zagrajmy w 2014 FIFA World Cup Brazil", tylko gameplay z pełnej wersji. Z okazji trwających Mistrzostw Świata postanowiłem rozegrać sobie mecz Belgia - Rosja, który dziś o godzinie 18:00 rozpocznie się na stadionie w Rio de Janeiro. 2014 FIFA World Cup Brazil zadebiutowało w naszym kraju 17 kwietnia 2014 roku za sprawą firmy Electronic Arts Polska na PlayStation 3 oraz Xboksie 360.

2014 FIFA World Cup Brazil to specjalna odsłona popularnej serii symulatorów piłki nożnej. Produkcja jest w całości poświęcona zbliżającym się Mistrzostwom Świata w Piłce Nożnej 2014, które odbędą się w dniach 12 czerwca - 13 lipca w Brazylii. Gra pozwala na wzięcie udziału w kwalifikacjach oraz samym turnieju, a także oferuje wiele innych trybów rozgrywki. No i jak zwykle dla graczy to świetna okazja, by wraz z Reprezentacją Polski zdobyć Puchar Świata, choćby wirtualnie;).

snippet.title: FIFA World Cup 2014. Destination: Manaus, Arena da Amazônia
snippet.description:
The very location of the city of Manaus is one of its most remarkable attractions: the confluence of the rivers Negro (Black) and Solimões (how the Amazon River is known in this part of Brazil). 

The city of Manaus is home to a majority of football clubs in the state of Amazonas and, therefore, several rivalries. Nacional Futebol Clube hold the record for most state titles, but over the last few years São Raimundo Esporte Clube have been drawing national attention with good performances in the Copa do Brasil. Other traditional contenders are Atletico Rio Negro Clube, Nacional Fast Club and America Futebol Clube. 

While not one of the traditional hotbeds of Brazilian football, Manaus is sure to prove a major attraction at Brazil 2014 thanks to the Arena Amazonia's unique position at the heart of the Amazon rainforest.

Manaus FIFA World Cup Game Schedule:

Match  Date / Time  Stage     Results   
8  14 June / 18:00  Group D  England - Italy
18  18 June / 18:00  Group A  Cameroon  - Croatia
30  22 June / 18:00  Group G  USA  - Portugal
41  25 June / 16:00  Group E  Honduras - Switzerland

#wc2014brasil #WC2014 #curitiba #football
http://www.teleprostir.com

Z okazji trwających Mistrzostw Świata postanowiłem rozegrać sobie mecz Nigeria - Argentyna, który dziś o godzinie 18:00 rozpocznie się na stadionie w Porto Alegre. 2014 FIFA World Cup Brazil zadebiutowało w naszym kraju 17 kwietnia 2014 roku za sprawą firmy Electronic Arts Polska na PlayStation 3 oraz Xboksie 360.

snippet.title: Germany World Cup 2014  Coach Joachim Low picks his nose then shakes Cristiano Ronaldo's hand after
snippet.description:
Just when it looked like the World Cup "dark horses" were about to turn up lame, Belgium turned on the power in the final straight to overcome Algeria 2-1 in Belo Horizonte.
Trailing to Sofiane Feghouli's first-half penalty, Belgium, tipped by many to reach the later stages of the tournament, hit back in impressive fashion.
Marouane Fellaini, derided for much of the season following a nightmare year at Manchester United, headed home an equalizer with 20 minutes remaining after entering the fray as a substitute.
And Belgium sealed victory with 10 minutes left when Dries Mertens rounded off a stylish counter-attack to snatch victory.
Much has been made of Marc Wilmots' side as the tournament's "dark horses" even if this is a nation which has not qualified for the World Cup since 2002.

The Netherlands were given a scare by Australia, but came from behind to win 3-2.

The Netherlands came from behind against Australia in Porto Alegre to record their second win of the group stages. The Socceroos certainly didn't make life easy for the Dutch, taking the lead through Mile Jedinak after Tim Cahill cancelled out Arjen Robben's opener. However, they largely failed to take their chances against a clinical Oranje, and goals from Robin van Persie and Memphis Depay ensured they were made to pay a heavy price.

snippet.title: Juan Mata - Dare to Predict - FIFA World Cup
snippet.description:
Watch Juan Mata's #DareToPredict video regarding his predictions on the Brazil 2014 FIFA World Cup. Now make a video reply with your predictions to our 5 World Cup questions for the chance to win top signed prizes!

Juan Manuel Mata García is a Spanish professional footballer who has played as a midfielder for Premier League club Manchester United since 2014 and the Spain national team since 2009.
Mata played for Real Madrid Castilla in 2006–07, before joining Valencia in the summer of 2007. He became an integral part of the club's midfield, making 174 appearances over the course of four seasons. In August 2011, Mata signed for English club Chelsea of the Premier League, and in his debut season, won the UEFA Champions League and the FA Cup. The following year, Chelsea won the UEFA Europa League, making Mata and teammate Fernando Torres the first players to hold the Champions League, Europa League, World Cup, and the European Championships simultaneously. Mata was later sold to Manchester United in January 2014, and has been part of Spain's National team since 2009.

snippet.title: Fifa World Cup 2014 with EyeCans Freestyle! (Animation)
snippet.description:
The Fifa World Cup happens once every 4 years and its the only time where people around the globe show their pride and celebrate their culture. If your country didn't make it, you have your next favourite team that you're rooting while hoping that the underdog makes it as well. Check us out @ http://culturelinx.com

Follow us on Twitter - http://twitter.com/Culturelinx
Visit our Shop - http://culturelinx.com/explore-the-marketplace/
Check out the EyeCans Website - http://eyecans.org

With that said, the concept of this video was born with the intent to connect the globe together. As this is an underlying philosophy of Culturelinx, along with bridging the culture gap, we decided to turn this into something fun that everyone can relate to. The video was done from start to finish in less than a month. 

What is Culturelinx™ anyway? 

The Culturelinx Project is aimed to help individuals connect with their culture, participate in local community events & initiatives, represent your pride, share & voice your views all while supporting your community through its local marketplace. This project was originally inspired as the founder and co-creator attended a festival of cultures in the local city where he grew up in Canada, called "Carassauga". This festival is an annual summer festival that is held every year targeted towards families and youth bringing together the multicultural spirit of Canada. 

To learn more about Culturelinx, show your pride and visit http://culturelinx.com 


What are EyeCans™ and where did they come from? 

The EyeCans™ came from another planet while a young man was day dreaming about how he could motivate young kids while creating a mascot for a student loyalty program. He recalled an earlier time in his life while in grade 5, a guest speaker had come to the school to give a speech on career paths and motivation. This speaker gave a tin can, a marker, and some masking tape to each student. She then proceeded to ask each student to write the letter, I, on the tin can, as a symbol that no matter what happens, if anyone tells you "You Can't Do Something" including your teachers, parents, coach, friends or yourself, look at this tin can, and say, "Yes, I Can!"... 

This "I Can Do" attitude remained with this young man and acted as inspiration to bring this character to life. To learn more about the EyeCans™ Project, visit http://eyecans.org

This project has been supported by Prepr Foundation (http://prepr.org) and is part of the summer PreprPIE Program (http://preprpie.org)

snippet.title: PM releases commemorative postage stamps on FIFA World Cup (Full speech)
snippet.description:
Prime Minister Narendra Modi today released commemorative postage stamps on the 2014 FIFA World Cup. On the occasion Prime Minister said sports bring about a spirit of amity and belonging among nations of the world.

The Prime Minister said that India is preparing to host the under-17 FIFA World Cup and also recalled the glorious history of football in India. He also urged the Department of Posts to also develop a website on the history of Indian football.

snippet.title: Claudia Leitte We Are One (Ola Ola) 2014 FIFA World Cup Official Song
snippet.description:
INTERVIEW to Claudia Leitte, singer of We Are One (ola ola), the new 2014 FIFA World Cup Official Song.
Brazilian singer Claudia Leitte talks about how she feels about singing at the Opening Ceremony of the FIFA World Cup on home soil, her passion for football and the partnership with Pitbull. She also sings part of the 2014 FIFA World Cup Official Song "We are one (Ole Ola)".

00:02-00:39: "I see the concert as a big introduction to the show will put on in the World Cup. Because we are very good at cheering and it influences everybody. So I'm one more fan, one more happy Brazilian that supports her country and believes it will be a great celebration. I'm of course anxious but I will have a lot of fun on stage. I'm a Brazilian fan convinced that everything will work great on that stage."

00:39-00:59: "It was great. It looked like we already knew each other. But actually the moments we met in person were very rare. We created the music basically by internet and n the phone. We got to know each other little by little but if we hadn't found chemistry we wouldn't have reached the same result."

00:59-01:30: "Pitbull loved the "cavaquinho" (a Brazilian kind of ukulele), so much we put it in the song. In the drums we also invited Olodum. He asked me "what's your favourite drummer's group in Brazil that must be with us?". I said Olodum, of course. He listened to it, I showed him the videos of Olodum with Michael Jackson and Paul Simon. He loved the fusion of styles. That's what makes me even happier, the interest for Brazilian our things. I'm loving it."

01:31-02:13: Claudia Leitte sings part of the official song.

02:13-03:00: "I'm Brazilian. I love football. I'm a supporter of Bahia, from my home place. I mostly follow my team, but I'm also a friend of Neymar and Daniel Alves. I support them a lot, since we're friends, just as I do with Kaká, who is also a friend of mine. So it's easier for me to follow the matches when Bahia or any of them is on the pitch, no matter the club they are playing for. But I'm like a coach, I give my opinion all the time. "

03:00-03:25: "I have already put it on my schedule. After Brazil matches I can't have any concert. There is no way I can spare my voice when my team is playing. So the day after if I have a concert I won't be ready. So there is no way I can schedule a concert the day after Brazil plays."

snippet.title: FIFA World Cup 2014. Destination: Curitiba, Arena da Baixada
snippet.description:
The city of Curitiba is one of the finest examples of a bulky economic and industrial development carried out with responsibility and organisation. 

Curitiba is home to two traditional clubs of Brazilian football: Coritiba Foot Ball Club and Clube Atletico Paranaense, who meet for one of the most exciting derbies in the country, the Atletiba - a reason for frenzy in Curitiba since the two teams' very first meeting in 1924. 

Ever since renovation works were completed in June 1999, the historic Estadio Joaquim Americo -- better known as the Arena da Baixada -- has been considered one of Brazil's most modern and best-appointed stadiums. 

Curitiba FIFA World Cup Game Schedule:

Match  Date / Time  Stage     Results   
12  16 June / 16:00  Group F  Iran - Nigeria
26  20 June / 19:00  Group E  Honduras - Ecuador
35  23 June / 13:00  Group B  Australia - Spain
48  26 June / 17:00  Group H  Algeria - Russia

It's updated to 2014 trending countries.

So, don't doubt and download it!

snippet.title: Adidas Brazuca: Final Rio vs. Classic | FIFA World Cup Ball | Comparison & Tech Talk
snippet.description:
Adidas Brazuca: Final Rio vs.  Classic - FIFA World Cup Ball
Comparison & Tech Talk - by Kreisliga-Legenden
GET THE BRAZUCA NOW: http://goo.gl/5WamfE

SUBSCRIBE: http://goo.gl/uZDGfy
Facebook: http://www.facebook.com/kreisligalegenden
Instagram: http://www.instagram.com/kreisligalegenden
Twitter: http://www.twitter.com/kl_legenden

YouTube: http://www.youtube.com/kreisligalegenden

Als der brazuca im Dezember 2013 lanciert wurde, lieferte adidas Exemplare an alle teilnehmenden Mitgliedsverbände der FIFA Fussball-Weltmeisterschaft Brasilien 2014™, um allen Teams genügend Zeit zu geben, sich sowohl im Training als auch in offiziellen Spielen mit dem neuen Ball vertraut zu machen. Seitdem hat der Ball bereits eine Paraderolle in Wettbewerben wie der FIFA Klub-Weltmeisterschaft, dem spanischen Pokalwettbewerb Copa del Rey, in der MLS, im DFB-Pokal sowie in zahlreichen internationalen Freundschaftsspielen gespielt. Seit Anfang Juni ist der Ball als offizieller WM-Ball in Brasilien im Einsatz. Kurz vor Beginn des Turniers hat adidas auch den Ball für das WM-Finale veröffentlicht: den brazuca Final Rio. Das Design des brazuca Final Rio wurde an die grün-goldene Farbgebung des FIFA WM-Pokals angelehnt und ist eine Variation des Offiziellen Spielballs adidas brazuca.

At the time of the brazuca launch in December, adidas delivered brazucas to all Participating Member Associations competing at Brazil 2014 in order for all teams to have sufficient time to practise with the new balls both in training and competitive matches. Since then, the ball has also played a starring role in competitions such as the FIFA Club World Cup, Copa del Rey, MLS, DFB-Pokal as well as numerous international friendlies. Since the beginning of June the brazuca is used as the official match ball of the FIFA World Cup 2014 in Brazil. Right before the beginning of the tournament adidas released another brazuca: the brazuca Final Rio, used on 13th July in the World Cup final match in Rio. The design of brazuca Final Rio has been inspired by the green and gold on the FIFA World Cup Trophy and is a variation of the previously released adidas brazuca Official Match Ball.

Since the beginning of June the brazuca is used as the official match ball of the FIFA World Cup 2014 in Brazil. Right before the beginning of the tournament adidas released another brazuca: the brazuca Final Rio, used on 13th July in the World Cup final match in Rio. The design of brazuca Final Rio has been inspired by the green and gold on the FIFA World Cup Trophy and is a variation of the previously released adidas brazuca Official Match Ball.
